  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2-Advancing the Right to Education for Children with Disability in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Hold a project inception meeting with project staff and partners to share project objectives and activities.  

2. Print 1000 copies of posters and simplified IE policy and disseminate to stakeholders

3. Hold a television or radio talk show (prime time) on at least 3 media platforms each quarter to educate the public and engender discussion on IE policy; increase pressure on government to increase budgetary allocation and disbursement for the implementation of the IE policy; highlight the importance of the role of parents in the education of children with disabilities and promote a paradigm shift from stigmatisation to support for children with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhanced access to quality pre-tertiary education for disadvantaged children especially children with disabilities by 2020.
1. An increase in the budgetary allocation for inclusive education from the current 0.5% to 2% of the education budget. An increase in in financing for inclusive education is also expected to help district officials and school heads to effectively implement the inclusive education policy and therefore children with disability will be able to access school facilities and have adequate learning materials for their needs.

2. It will also help to increase the knowledge of district officials, school heads, teachers, school management teams and other relevant stakeholders about the IE. An increase in knowledge is will be instrumental in engendering more positive attitudes and behaviours towards persons with disability as well as compliance with the policy by duty bearers.</narrative>
  </description>
